{{Infobox recurring event |name = Calgary International Reggae Festival |logo = |image = Calgary-reggae-fest-2006-panoramic.jpg |caption = Calgary International Reggae Fest 2006 |location = [[Millennium Park (Calgary)|Millennium Park]], [[Calgary]] |years_active = 2004–present |founded = |dates = Mid August |genre = [[Music festival]] |patron = Calgary Reggae Festival Society |website = {{URL|www.ReggaeFest.ca}} }} The '''Calgary International Reggae Festival''' is an annual event in [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]], [[Canada]] that is organized by the Calgary Reggae Festival Society.
Featuring a mixture of local and international reggae acts, the festival has taken place every year since 2004.<ref name="Wilton">Wilton, Lisa (2103) "[http://metronews.ca/uncategorized/766928/calgary-international-reggae-festival-celebrates-10-crazy-years-of-mostly-happy-times/ Calgary International Reggae Festival celebrates 10 crazy years of (mostly) happy times]", [[Metro News]], August 14, 2013. Retrieved June 20, 2014</ref> Starting as a one-day event, by 2008 it had expanded to a ten-day festival.<ref name="Wilton" /> The festival was co-founded by Leo Cripps, the host of [[CJSW-FM]]'s ''Caribbean Link-Up'' show, and from an early stage it was sponsored by radio station [[Vibe 98.5]].<ref name="FFWD">Stewart, M.D. (2007) "[http://www.ffwdweekly.com/article/music/music-previews/hot-fun-summertime/ Hot Fun in the Summertime] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714172903/http://www.ffwdweekly.com/article/music/music-previews/hot-fun-summertime/# |date=2014-07-14 }}", ''[[Fast Forward Weekly]]'', August 9, 2007. Retrieved June 20, 2014</ref>
The 2014 event was headlined by [[Third World (band)|Third World]].<ref name="Bell">Bell, Mike (2014) "[http://blogs.calgaryherald.com/2014/03/13/calgary-international-reggaefest-announces-third-world-as-early-headliner/ Calgary International ReggaeFest announces Third World as early headliner]", ''[[Calgary Herald]]'', March 13, 2014. Retrieved June 20, 2014</ref>
