The '''National Farm Machinery Show''' is an [[agricultural machinery]] exposition held annually in February indoors at the [[Kentucky Exposition Center]] in [[Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville]], [[Kentucky]], United States.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=dbNBAAAAIBAJ&sjid=qKkMAAAAIBAJ&pg=5306,2386120&dq=national-farm-machinery-show&hl=en |title=Farm-machinery Show Opens Tomorrow |agency=Associated Press |date=February 12, 1985 |work=Daily News |location=Middlesboro, Kentucky |accessdate=December 31, 2011}}</ref><ref name="fd20090217">{{cite news |url=http://www.farmanddairy.com/news/national-farm-machinery-show-visitors-exhibitors-cautiously-optimistic/11254.html |title=National Farm Machinery Show visitors, exhibitors 'cautiously optimistic' |last=Crowell |first=Susan |date=February 17, 2009 |work=Farm and Dairy |accessdate=December 31, 2011}}</ref> Attendance exceeds 300,000 people, with 800 exhibitors in display space of {{convert|1200000|sqft|m2}}.<ref>[http://www.farmmachineryshow.org/nfms/the_show/forty_facts.htm NFMS Fact Sheet]</ref><ref name="edr19850214">{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=mJlUAAAAIBAJ&sjid=R48DAAAAIBAJ&pg=2298,4721684&dq=national-farm-machinery-show&hl=en |title=Farm show opens |date=February 14, 1985 |work=The Daily Record |accessdate= December 31, 2011 |location=Ellensburg, Washington}}</ref>
The show started as an electricity demonstration and exhibit in 1963, and adopted the name National Farm Machinery Show in 1966.<ref name="fd20030220">{{cite news |url=http://www.farmanddairy.com/news/electricity-show-sparks-indoor-farm-spectacular/90.html |title=Electricity show sparks indoor farm spectacular |last=Crowell |first=Susan |date=February 20, 2003 |work=Farm and Dairy |accessdate=December 31, 2011}}</ref>
The National Farm Machinery Show includes the Championship Tractor Pull, an annual event since 1969. {{citation needed|date=January 2012}}
