{{Infobox referendum |name = All-Russia referendum about introduction of a post of the President of the RSFSR |title = Do You consider it necessary to introduce the post of [[President of Russia|President of the RSFSR]] elected by popular vote? |location = [[Russian SFSR]] |date = 17 March 1991 |yes = 53,385,275 |yespct = 71.4 |no = 21,406,152 |nopct = 28.6 |valid = 74,791,427 |validpct = 97.9 |invalid = 1,633,683 |invalidpct = 2.1 |total = 76,425,110 |totalpct = 100 |turnoutpct = 75.1 |electorate = 101,776,550 |map = 1991 Russian presidential referendum.svg |legend_yes = #00b300 |legend_no = #ff0000 }} {{Politics of Russia}}
A '''referendum on creating the post of [[President of Russia]]''' was held in [[Russia]] on 17 March 1991.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p1642 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> The referendum was held alongside a [[Soviet Union referendum, 1991|referendum of the preservation of USSR]]. Prior to the referendum, the Russian [[head of state]] was the [[Chairman of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the Russian SFSR|Chairman of the Supreme Soviet of the Russian SFSR]], elected by the [[Congress of People's Deputies of Russia|Congress of People's Deputies of the Russian SFSR]]. With 71.4% of voters approving the proposal, the post of President of the Russian SFSR was introduced, and two months later [[Boris Yeltsin]] was [[Russian presidential election, 1991|elected]] as the first president.
==Question== {{blockquote|Do you consider it necessary to introduce the post of [[President of Russia|President of the RSFSR]] elected by popular vote?<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p1647</ref><ref>[http://new.hse.ru/sites/tp/isakov/1990-1996dn/71/1/Сообщение%20об%20итогах%20референдума%20РСФСР%2017%20марта%201991%20года.htm Сообщение Центральной комиссии РСФСР по проведению референдумов] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108000403/http://new.hse.ru/sites/tp/isakov/1990-1996dn/71/1/%D0%A1%D0%BE%D0%BE%D0%B1%D1%89%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%B5%20%D0%BE%D0%B1%20%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%BE%D0%B3%D0%B0%D1%85%20%D1%80%D0%B5%D1%84%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B4%D1%83%D0%BC%D0%B0%20%D0%A0%D0%A1%D0%A4%D0%A1%D0%A0%2017%20%D0%BC%D0%B0%D1%80%D1%82%D0%B0%201991%20%D0%B3%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B0.htm |date=2012-01-08 }}</ref>}}
