{{World-Scrabble-Championship | year=2013 | date-from=3 December 2013| date-to=8 December 2013| location=Andel's Hotel, Prague, Czech Republic | winner=[[Nigel Richards (Scrabble)]] | number-of-players=110 | sponsor=Mattel | previous=2011 | next=2014 }}
The '''World Scrabble Championship 2013''', renamed by Mattel to '''Scrabble Champions Tournament''', was held in Andel's Hotel, [[Prague]], [[Czech Republic]] during December 2013.<ref>http://www.wespa.org/news/2013xchampions.shtml</ref>
The format was a 31-round preliminary tournament and best-of-five semi-finals and final. After defeating [[Dave Wiegand]] and [[Sammy Okosagah]] in the semi-finals respectively, [[Nigel Richards (Scrabble)|Nigel Richards]] and [[Komol Panyasophonlert]] played a best-of-five final for the top prize and the title of World Scrabble Champion 2013.<ref>http://event.poslfit.com/2013/sct/</ref>
==Results== The winner was Nigel Richards of [[New Zealand]] who defeated Komol Panyasophonlert of [[Thailand]] with three games to two in the best-of-five finals.<ref>http://forum.mindsportsinternational.com/yaf_postst508p2_Prague-Mind-Sports-Festival---Highlights.aspx?=</ref> Richards set the record for being the first three-time World Champion, the only person to have won the title more than once.
In a lucky start with two blanks, Komol started with a 70 point bingo [[wikt:poonac|POONAcs]]. Nigel replied immediately with a 94 point bingo [[wikt:diatonic|DIATONIC]], to set the tone for a high standard final. Komol had further bingos [[wikt:douleia|DOULEIAS]], EXALTERS and LIGHTENS while Nigel had [[wikt:terrapin|TERRAPIN]]. Komol won the first game 495 - 445.
In the second game, Nigel saved his X to hook his own word [[wikt:jeu|JEU]] to make a 73 point EXACT with JEUX. Nigel had bingos OUTDARED and NOISIER. Komol tried to pull back a large lead with a 107 point phony HALVINGS on the triple, but it was successfully challenged and Nigel won the game 471 - 319.
In the third game, Komol set the pace with a 66 point [[wikt:qat|QAT]]. Komol had bingos [[wikt:aerogel|AEROGEL]], [[wikt:seiten|SEITENS]] and [[wikt:ordinant|ORDINAnT]] while Nigel clawed back with yARNERS and a 75 point JACKS on the triple word. It was not enough and Komol won 471 - 433.
In the fourth game, Komol's first play was PARTAKeN for 68 and Nigel immediately replied with [[wikt:adnation|ADNATiON]] for 82, not having had a chance to use his blank for a bingo in his first turn. Nigel had further bingos INCENTS and PILOTAGE, a 63 point [[wikt:qi|QI]] and [[wikt:shoji|SHOJIS]] for 72 while Komol tried to come back with [[wikt:suetier|SUETIER]] but to no avail. Nigel won 518 - 410, to pull the score back to 2-2 with one game remaining to decide the title.
In the final game, Komol had a great start with [[wikt:gazump|GAZUMPED]] for 96 but Nigel responded with BEJEWeL for 89 and [[wikt:aurorean|AUrOREAN]] across six hooks for 98 to take a 100+ lead. Komol had a vowel heavy rack of AEEIIIT and exchanged AEIII. Nigel had bingo OILSEED and a 60 point [[wikt:grex|GREX]] while Komol eventually found bingo [[wikt:viremia|VIREMIAS]] after successive bad draws. Nigel sealed the win with [[wikt:ratooner|RATOONER]] with a final score of 581 - 421,<ref>http://event.poslfit.com/games/sct2013/</ref> thus clinching the title of World Champion for the third time, the only person to have won it more than once.
